Representative UEBA & Detection Use Cases

  • Privileged Account Misuse: After-hours admin access, privilege escalation, unusual locations, and high-volume command activity.
  • High-Risk Transactions & Anomalies: Unusual high-value activity outside normal patterns, volume spikes, and sudden behavior changes on critical systems.
  • Credential Sharing & Session Misuse: Concurrent logins from impossible locations, shared credentials, and abnormal session patterns across key applications.
  • Suspicious Authentication Activity: First-time access to sensitive apps, access from restricted geographies, abnormal time-of-day, and geo-velocity violations.
  • Data Exfiltration: Abnormal download volumes, unauthorized file and database access, DLP violations, and unusual query patterns.
  • Insider Threat Indicators: Sensitive HR/finance access before separation, mass data access prior to termination, and lateral movement across tiers.
  • MFA Fatigue & Identity Threats: Excessive denies then approval, push spam campaigns, and authentications from new devices without expected MFA context.
